Extract events (things that happened or were done) from the following text. Return a JSON array.
Each event must have these fields:
- "event_type": category like "configuration", "installation", "migration", "deployment", "debugging", "creation", "update", "deletion", "backup", "monitoring"
- "summary": one-line description of what happened
- "actors": array of entity names involved (who did it)
- "objects": array of entity names affected (what was affected)
- "location": entity name of where it happened (server, container, etc.) or null
- "time_ref": any time reference from the text (date, "yesterday", "phase 3", etc.) or null
- "confidence": float 0.0-1.0

Rules:
- Focus on actions and changes, not static facts
- Include infrastructure events: deployments, configurations, migrations
- Include troubleshooting events: debugging, fixing, investigating

Text:
{{ text }}

Return ONLY a valid JSON array, no other text.